{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MwjjpC541gtjPuVyuVQViE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n2\t# Task: doc-1\n3\t\n4\t## Goal\n5\tGenerate documentation for the user-service source tree. Produce companion `.md`\n6\tfiles for every source file, a `README.md` in every directory, and cross-component\n7\tsynthesis docs (`data-flow.md`) at composite levels.\n8\t\n9\tThe source tree is a Go HTTP service with the following structure:\n10\t\n11\t```\n12\tmain.go                                    ← service entry point\n13\tinternal/userservice/\n14\t  store/\n15\t    store.go                               ← in-memory user store\n16\t  handlers/\n17\t    handlers.go                            ← HTTP CRUD handlers\n18\t```\n19\t\n20\t## Context\n21\tThis is a regression test for the ai-builder doc pipeline.\n22\t\n23\tThe pipeline must:\n24\t- Traverse the source tree recursively\n25\t- At each leaf directory (atomic): read source files, write companion `.md` files\n26\t  and a `README.md` describing the package\n27\t- At each composite directory (after all leaves complete): write cross-component\n28\t  synthesis docs (`data-flow.md`, `README.md`) using the completed sub-component\n29\t  handoff summaries\n30\t- Never modify source files — only create `.md` files\n31\t\n32\tThe output directory IS the source tree. All generated `.md` files are written\n33\tinline alongside the source files they document.\n34\t\n35\t## Components\n36\t\n37\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n38\t\n39\t## Design\n40\t\n41\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n42\t\n43\t## Acceptance Criteria\n44\t\n45\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n46\t\n47\t## Test Command\n48\t\n49\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n50\t\n51\t## Suggested Tools\n52\t\n53\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n54\t\n55\t## Notes\n56\t\n57\t_None._\n58\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c